steps.description:
Fix the type_system_inconsistency in crates/reify-constraints/src/classifier.rs (reviewer: architect_reviewer). In the `CompiledExprKind::ValueRef` arm of `collect_flags` (lines 80-87), replace the manual type match with the type system's canonical `is_numeric()` method. Change from:
```rust
match &expr.result_type {
    Type::Bool => flags.has_logical = true,
    Type::Int | Type::Real | Type::Scalar { .. } | Type::String => {
        flags.has_numeric = true;
    }
}
```
To:
```rust
if expr.result_type.is_numeric() {
    flags.has_numeric = true;
} else if expr.result_type == Type::Bool {
    flags.has_logical = true;
}
// Type::String is a no-op — no domain flag set, consistent with Type::is_numeric()
```
This aligns with the canonical `Type::is_numeric()` definition in reify-types/src/ty.rs:42 which returns `matches!(self, Type::Int | Type::Real | Type::Scalar { .. })`, explicitly excluding String. Verify all existing classifier tests plus the new step-15 regression tests pass.

Implement `CompiledExpr::walk` method in `crates/reify-types/src/expr.rs` (reviewer: reviewer_reuse_auditor — addressing code duplication concern).

Add to the `impl CompiledExpr` block:
```rust
/// Recursively walk the expression tree, calling `f` on each node (pre-order).
///
/// This is the canonical traversal for `CompiledExprKind`. All callers
/// that need to visit expression nodes should use this method rather than
/// implementing their own match on `CompiledExprKind`. This ensures that
/// when new variants are added, only this single method needs updating.
pub fn walk(&self, f: &mut impl FnMut(&CompiledExpr)) {
    f(self);
    match &self.kind {
        CompiledExprKind::Literal(_) => {}
        CompiledExprKind::ValueRef(_) => {}
        CompiledExprKind::BinOp { left, right, .. } => {
            left.walk(f);
            right.walk(f);
        }
        CompiledExprKind::UnOp { operand, .. } => {
            operand.walk(f);
        }
        CompiledExprKind::FunctionCall { args, .. } => {
            for arg in args {
                arg.walk(f);
            }
        }
        CompiledExprKind::Conditional { condition, then_branch, else_branch } => {
            condition.walk(f);
            then_branch.walk(f);
            else_branch.walk(f);
        }
    }
}
```

Verify all step-19 tests pass.

Refactor `collect_value_refs` in `crates/reify-constraints/src/decompose.rs` to use `CompiledExpr::walk`, eliminating the duplicated match on `CompiledExprKind` (reviewer: reviewer_reuse_auditor).

Replace the manual 6-arm match in `collect_value_refs` (lines 72-99) with:
```rust
fn collect_value_refs(expr: &CompiledExpr, out: &mut HashSet<ValueCellId>) {
    expr.walk(&mut |node| {
        if let CompiledExprKind::ValueRef(id) = &node.kind {
            out.insert(id.clone());
        }
    });
}
```

This delegates all child traversal to `CompiledExpr::walk`. When new variants are added to `CompiledExprKind`, only `walk()` needs updating — `collect_value_refs` automatically handles them.

Verify all existing decompose tests (including step-21) pass. The `collect_value_refs_pub` wrapper needs no change — it delegates to the same function.

Refactor `collect_flags` in `crates/reify-constraints/src/classifier.rs` to use `CompiledExpr::walk`, eliminating the duplicated match on `CompiledExprKind` (reviewer: reviewer_reuse_auditor).

Replace the manual 6-arm match in `collect_flags` (lines 67-116) with:
```rust
fn collect_flags(expr: &CompiledExpr, flags: &mut DomainFlags) {
    expr.walk(&mut |node| {
        match &node.kind {
            CompiledExprKind::Literal(value) => {
                match value {
                    Value::Bool(_) => flags.has_logical = true,
                    Value::Int(_) | Value::Real(_) | Value::Scalar { .. } => {
                        flags.has_numeric = true;
                    }
                    Value::String(_) | Value::Undef => {}
                }
            }
            CompiledExprKind::ValueRef(_) => {
                if node.result_type.is_numeric() {
                    flags.has_numeric = true;
                } else if node.result_type == Type::Bool {
                    flags.has_logical = true;
                }
            }
            CompiledExprKind::FunctionCall { function, .. } => {
                if is_geometry_qualified_name(&function.qualified_name) {
                    flags.has_geometric = true;
                }
            }
            // Child traversal handled by walk — no manual recursion needed
            _ => {}
        }
    });
}
```

This delegates all child traversal to `CompiledExpr::walk`. The classifier only inspects domain-relevant node kinds (Literal, ValueRef, FunctionCall) and ignores structural nodes (BinOp, UnOp, Conditional) since their domain contribution comes from their children.

Verify all existing classifier tests (including step-23) pass.
